Sir Richard Vautort, master of the college, says that according to the original charter of erectiori and *the statutes of the college also there should be in the college twelve chaplain fellows and a master ; and now there are only twelve in all.1 Likewise there should be four gentlemen clerks and four yeomen clerks, and now there are but six. Also there should be thirteen choristers‚ and now there are but ten ; and interro- gated concerning the reason of the decline of numbers, he says that the rents and goods of the college have grown to so little that they are hardly or are not sufficient for the maintenance for the number that now is.
